  "tips": [
    "Benasque occupies the central valley of the three that make up the Posets-Maladeta Natural Park. From this town with a lot of soul you can enjoy the Pyrenean landscape. Not only that, but it is home to the largest number of 3,000-meter-high peaks in the mountain range.\r\n\r\nThe Benasque Valley forms the center and heart of the Pyrenees.",
    "Estibafreda Peak at 2694m in the Benasque Valley.",
    "Here you will find a small high mountain lake with spectacular views around it.",
    "The most spectacular part of the descent from Sierra Negra.",
    "This is a nice trail that is mostly single track. The perfect way to start or end a longer mountain bike ride or just as part of a small loop."
